        "text": "*[Bug 18989] Wishlist: provide conversion of POSIXlt time zone retaining sub-second accuracy*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18989>\n\n--- Comment #4 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---\n(In reply to Suharto Anggono from comment #1)\nI would expect that full precision is also kept for input that is a vector of\ncharacter strings. To accomplish it,\n    x &lt;- list(...)\ncan be changed to\n    x &lt;- lapply(list(...), function(x)\n                if(is.character(x) || is.factor(x)) as.POSIXlt(x) else x)",
